## 🛠️ Quick Start

### Get Your API Key

1. Sign up on [RapidAPI](https://rapidapi.com)
2. Subscribe to the **Phone Validation API**
3. Copy your `X-RapidAPI-Key` header

### Test the API (cURL)

```bash
# Single phone validation
curl --request GET \
  --url 'https://phone-validation-api.onrender.com/validate?phone=%2B14155552671' \
  --header 'X-RapidAPI-Key: YOUR_API_KEY' \
  --header 'X-RapidAPI-Host: phone-validation-api.p.rapidapi.com'

# Batch validation (up to 100 numbers)
curl --request POST \
  --url 'https://phone-validation-api.onrender.com/validate/batch' \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --header 'X-RapidAPI-Key: YOUR_API_KEY' \
  --data '["+14155552671", "+380671234567", "+442071234567"]'

  ## 📚 API Endpoints

### Public Endpoints (No Auth Required)

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET | `/` | API information and pricing |
| GET | `/health` | Health check |
| GET | `/legal/gdpr` | GDPR compliance information |

### Protected Endpoints (Require API Key)

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET | `/validate` | Validate a single phone number |
| POST | `/validate/batch` | Validate up to 100 numbers |
| POST | `/bulk/upload` | Upload CSV for bulk validation |
| GET | `/usage` | View your usage statistics |
| GET | `/stats` | API performance statistics |
| POST | `/webhooks/register` | Register a webhook URL |
| GET | `/webhooks` | List your webhooks |
| DELETE | `/webhooks/{id}` | Delete a webhook |

---

## 🔧 Local Development
Prerequisites
Python 3.11+

Installation
bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/phone-validation-api.git
cd phone-validation-api

# Create virtual environment
python3.11 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Run the API
python main.py
The API will be available at http://localhost:8005

Environment Variables
Variable	Default	Description
ENVIRONMENT	development	Set to production for deployment
PORT	8005	Port the API runs on
