🚢 Deployment
Deploy to Render
Push your code to GitHub

Log into Render.com

Click "New +" → "Web Service"

Connect your GitHub repository

Set:

Build Command: pip install -r requirements.txt

Start Command: python main.py

Environment Variable: ENVIRONMENT=production

Click "Create Web Service"

Add to RapidAPI
Go to RapidAPI

Click "Add New API"

Set your Render URL as the base URL

Configure pricing plans

Publish

🔒 GDPR Compliance
✅ No phone numbers are permanently stored

✅ Usage logs are anonymized after 30 days

✅ No data is sold to third parties

✅ Full compliance with GDPR requirements

View full GDPR statement

📊 Example Responses
Single Validation (Valid)
json
{
  "phone": "+380671234567",
  "valid": true,
  "possible": true,
  "formatted_number": "+380671234567",
  "country_code": 380,
  "national_number": "671234567",
  "carrier": "Kyivstar",
  "timezone": ["Europe/Kyiv"],
  "location": "Ukraine"
}
Single Validation (Invalid)
json
{
  "detail": {
    "error": "INVALID_PHONE_FORMAT",
    "message": "Missing or invalid default region.",
    "example": "+14155552671"
  }
}
Batch Validation
json
{
  "total": 3,
  "valid_count": 2,
  "results": [
    {"phone": "+14155552671", "valid": true, "carrier": "AT&T"},
    {"phone": "invalid", "valid": false, "error": "Invalid format"},
    {"phone": "+380671234567", "valid": true, "carrier": "Kyivstar"}
  ],
  "batch_id": "20260420194251"
}
❓ Frequently Asked Questions
How accurate is the validation?
The API uses Google's phonenumbers library — the same library that powers Android phones. Accuracy is 99.9%+ for valid number detection.

What countries are supported?
200+ countries — every country with a valid country code.

How is this cheaper than Twilio?
Twilio charges $0.05 per validation ($50 per 1k). We charge $0.019 per validation ($19 per 1k) — 62% cheaper.

Do you store phone numbers?
No. Phone numbers are validated in real-time and not stored. Only anonymized usage counts are kept.

Can I use this for SMS marketing?
Yes. Carrier detection helps you identify mobile numbers for SMS campaigns.

What happens if I exceed my rate limit?
You'll receive a 429 Rate Limit Exceeded error. Upgrade your plan for higher limits.

